How to Force/Prioritize German Language in Radarr or Sonarr you can tweak this to any language.
Step 1: Create the Custom Format
Open the menu on the left side of the UI.

Navigate to Settings > Custom Formats.

Click the + (Add New) button.

Name the new format German.

Under "Conditions," select Language Custom.

Configure the condition:

Name: German

Language: German

Required: Check this box (This is crucial to ensure only German releases are grabbed).

Click Save.

Step 2: Apply to Your Quality Profile
Go to Settings > Profiles.

Select the profile you assign to new downloads (e.g., Any, HD - 1080p, or your custom profile).

On the right side, look for the Custom Formats list.

Find your new German format in the list.

Set the score to 10 (or higher than any other custom format scores you have).

Optional: Ensure the Minimum Custom Format Score for the profile is set to 0.

Pro Tip: If you want Radarr/Sonarr to automatically upgrade your existing library to German versions, check the Upgrades Allowed box inside the profile settings before saving.
